column1: SDG 3.2 By 2030, end preventable deaths of newborns and children under 5 years of age, with all countries aiming to reduce neonatal mortality to at least as low as 12 per 1,000 live births and under-5 mortality to at least as low as 25 per 1,000 live births
Definition: Probability of dying between birth and exactly age 5, expressed per 1,000 live births.
Source: UN Inter-agency Group for Child Mortality Estimation (2019). Child mortality estimates. www.childmortality.org. Accessed 26 August 2020.

column2: Organization for Economic Co-operation and Development
